1
00:00:00,966 --> 00:00:02,200
if you're watching this video

2
00:00:02,200 --> 00:00:04,333
you are probably wondering what this game is about

3
00:00:04,666 --> 00:00:07,133
maybe you have already been told great things about this game

4
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:09,600
or maybe you have been impressed by some of its videos

5
00:00:09,733 --> 00:00:11,966
but I think the best description of this game is that

6
00:00:11,966 --> 00:00:14,166
it feels incredibly rewarding and meaningful

7
00:00:14,466 --> 00:00:16,600
but let's see what this game is actually about

8
00:00:16,733 --> 00:00:17,966
since it's a Minecraft modpack

9
00:00:17,966 --> 00:00:19,566
you start in the middle of nowhere

10
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:21,066
all you're given is a guidebook

11
00:00:21,066 --> 00:00:23,900
that contains all of the required information to complete the game

12
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:25,066
at the beginning

13
00:00:25,066 --> 00:00:26,833
you will have to survive the wild animals

14
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:28,966
while also trying to maintain a balanced diet

15
00:00:29,666 --> 00:00:32,766
then you will go through all of the steps of the industrial and silicon revolution

16
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:36,600
reaching sci-fi technologies up to the point of finally crafting a Stargate

17
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:38,666
but doing so is not too easy

18
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:44,933
every new age will indeed unlock new kinds of machines that will require new sorts of understandings to be successfully operated

19
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:48,333
you will have to explore many new planets to collect rare materials

20
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:51,566
that will require huge complex machine construction to be fully refined

21
00:00:52,133 --> 00:00:53,966
and while each step will solve a past issue

22
00:00:53,966 --> 00:00:56,933
it will open countless new possibilities and tasks to accomplish

23
00:00:57,200 --> 00:01:00,066
but saying it this way doesn't make justice to this game

24
00:01:00,166 --> 00:01:01,300
because as they say

25
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:03,400
the real joy isn't in the reaching the destination

26
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:05,000
but in the journey itself

27
00:01:05,133 --> 00:01:05,933
with that said

28
00:01:05,933 --> 00:01:07,933
let's now see what makes this journey special

29
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:13,266
GTNH is famous for its incredibly high waiting times

30
00:01:13,733 --> 00:01:17,066
while some people consider this its main weakness for how the game is designed

31
00:01:17,066 --> 00:01:18,733
that's actually one of its strengths

32
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:22,366
that's because the game will force you into actually understanding what's going on

33
00:01:22,366 --> 00:01:24,766
and then let you decide how you want to deal with it

34
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:25,966
for example

35
00:01:25,966 --> 00:01:27,966
making your first steel will require 1 hour

36
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,533
and the amount produced this way will be basically nothing

37
00:01:30,933 --> 00:01:33,466
this should push the player into building more Blast Furnaces

38
00:01:33,466 --> 00:01:36,000
and designing all that's required to keep those furnaces working

39
00:01:36,666 --> 00:01:38,600
however, overdoing it will cause new issues

40
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:40,133
such as excessive pollution

41
00:01:40,166 --> 00:01:43,166
which will then require additional effort to be properly managed

42
00:01:43,166 --> 00:01:47,866
otherwise, one could also use those waiting times to expand one of the many extra optional activities

43
00:01:47,866 --> 00:01:50,766
that will still provide some nice quality of life improvements

44
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:52,533
exponential growth

45
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,900
this is my favorite thing in GTNH

46
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,533
things scale incredibly quickly

47
00:01:56,933 --> 00:01:59,600
after many hours spent manually managing a steel workshop

48
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:04,600
we finally managed to build a fully automated Electric Blast Furnace capable of working 70 times faster

49
00:02:05,100 --> 00:02:06,466
and it still can be upgraded

50
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:09,800
we can upgrade it with better materials and more precise circuitry

51
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:14,000
allowing it to work at higher temperatures to speed up the process by hundreds of times

52
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:16,733
but at some point this still won't be enough

53
00:02:16,866 --> 00:02:18,500
so we can build a bigger version

54
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:22,066
capable of working thousands of ingots at a time and at super high speeds

55
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:25,366
finally, in the endgame we will unlock the Forge of the Gods

56
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:27,633
this incredible multiblock has its own skill tree

57
00:02:27,633 --> 00:02:31,533
where we can purchase upgrades with points we make by expanding or using it

58
00:02:31,666 --> 00:02:34,066
and that's how we make trillions of steel ingots

59
00:02:34,766 --> 00:02:35,600
gameplay length

60
00:02:36,066 --> 00:02:38,266
the next thing GTNH is famous for is that

61
00:02:38,266 --> 00:02:40,066
it takes thousands of hours to complete

62
00:02:40,133 --> 00:02:41,100
that's not a downside

63
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:44,766
but just something that you can enjoy without it finishing before you realize

64
00:02:45,466 --> 00:02:46,300
complexity

65
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:49,600
finally, the main selling point of GTNH is its complexity

66
00:02:49,900 --> 00:02:52,800
this game isn't hard as in requiring a particular skill

67
00:02:52,866 --> 00:02:56,166
but in the incredible level of problem solving and dedication required

68
00:02:56,366 --> 00:03:00,066
the first real challenge you'll find is probably managing your power network

69
00:03:00,366 --> 00:03:00,933
in most games

70
00:03:00,933 --> 00:03:03,066
you just connect everything to a main power line without really worrying about it too much

71
00:03:03,066 --> 00:03:04,866
（向上合并）

72
00:03:04,866 --> 00:03:06,400
but here things are more pronounced

73
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:11,066
so much that you will eventually get lost in labyrinths of cables that you will have to build

74
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:13,866
from the beginning you can choose from a huge variety of cables

75
00:03:14,066 --> 00:03:16,000
each one with a different cost and stats

76
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:18,566
and if you pick a cable that can't do the job

77
00:03:18,566 --> 00:03:20,066
it will eventually catch fire

78
00:03:20,366 --> 00:03:22,500
and that could cause other problems too

79
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,100
each cable also has a different resistance

80
00:03:25,266 --> 00:03:26,766
causing a different voltage drop

81
00:03:26,766 --> 00:03:28,066
which could hinder machines

82
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:31,100
each recipe indeed has a minimum power requirement

83
00:03:31,133 --> 00:03:32,366
and if it's not met

84
00:03:32,466 --> 00:03:35,933
the machine will get jammed and start the process all over again

85
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:38,266
but that's just the best case scenario

86
00:03:38,466 --> 00:03:42,000
bigger machines will get jammed to the point where manual intervention will be required

87
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:45,100
and the items that were being processed will be completely destroyed

88
00:03:45,733 --> 00:03:48,500
and if that was in a crafting chain with some looping byproducts

89
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:50,100
that will make the issue even worse

90
00:03:50,533 --> 00:03:51,766
but even worse is the case

91
00:03:51,766 --> 00:03:55,700
in which you accidentally give too much voltage to a machine that can't handle it

92
00:03:55,966 --> 00:03:59,366
and those were just the basics of proper power management in GregTech

93
00:03:59,366 --> 00:04:02,966
which as far as I know are already way far and beyond what most games do

94
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:06,466
another complex wiring management task is a AE2

95
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:07,400
if you didn't know

96
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:12,100
Applied Energistics is a mod used for managing resources by almost every Minecraft modpack

97
00:04:12,266 --> 00:04:16,266
not only this mod allows you to view all of what you have in your chests, warehouses and tanks

98
00:04:16,266 --> 00:04:17,766
it also restocks other machines

99
00:04:17,766 --> 00:04:20,566
and even allows for crafting things on demand or passively

100
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:24,666
this model alone in its original form already deserves a multi-video series

101
00:04:24,666 --> 00:04:29,166
but GTNH adds extra features to push even farther to manage GTNH's tasks

102
00:04:30,266 --> 00:04:34,100
next part of the game that some people consider complex is some of the processing lines 

103
00:04:34,266 --> 00:04:40,066
which often times will require you to concatenate dozens of machines to refine a single last out of an ore

104
00:04:40,066 --> 00:04:46,666
one more task that is usually considered a little bit complicated is figuring out how to solve some of the puzzles required to operate some of the machines

105
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:51,533
indeed, in GTNH it's quite common to find yourself coding something using diagram blocks

106
00:04:51,566 --> 00:04:52,933
working with redstone circuitries

107
00:04:52,933 --> 00:04:53,966
or making a spreadsheet

108
00:04:53,966 --> 00:04:56,866
or even graphs to figure out how to make something work properly

109
00:04:57,066 --> 00:04:57,733
and with that

110
00:04:57,733 --> 00:05:01,566
I think I managed to scratch the surface of what's needed to know about this game

111
00:05:01,966 --> 00:05:03,133
if you want to know more about it

112
00:05:03,133 --> 00:05:04,066
I made other videos

113
00:05:04,066 --> 00:05:07,766
and the community is one of the most friendly I have ever seen

114
00:05:07,766 --> 00:05:10,300
and thus, it's up to you to join us（向下分句）bye bye

115
00:00:00,966 --> 00:00:02,200
如果你正在看这期视频

116
00:00:02,200 --> 00:00:04,333
你大概想知道这个整合包到底在玩什么

117
00:00:04,666 --> 00:00:07,133
也许你已经听别人把它夸上天

118
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:09,600
或者你看过一些视频后被它震撼到了

119
00:00:09,733 --> 00:00:11,966
但在我看来，对它最好的描述是

120
00:00:11,966 --> 00:00:14,166
它会带来极强的成就感和意义感

121
00:00:14,466 --> 00:00:16,600
不过先来看看这游戏本身到底是什么

122
00:00:16,733 --> 00:00:17,966
因为它是一个 MC 整合包

123
00:00:17,966 --> 00:00:19,566
你会在荒郊野岭白手起家

124
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:21,066
给你提供的只有一本任务书

125
00:00:21,066 --> 00:00:23,900
里面包含通关所需的全部信息

126
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:25,066
游戏前期

127
00:00:25,066 --> 00:00:26,833
你得先荒野求生

128
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:28,966
同时保持饮食均衡

129
00:00:29,666 --> 00:00:32,766
接着你会走完整个工业革命与硅基革命的流程

130
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:36,600
科技一路攀升到最终做出星门

131
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:38,666
但这条路并不轻松

132
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:44,933
每个新时代都会解锁需要全新理解才能使用的新机器

133
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:48,333
你还得探索许多新行星，收集稀有材料

134
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:51,566
并建造庞大而复杂的产线来精炼它们

135
00:00:52,133 --> 00:00:53,966
虽然每一步都在解决过去的问题

136
00:00:53,966 --> 00:00:56,933
却也会同时打开无数新的可能和新的任务

137
00:00:57,200 --> 00:01:00,066
但光这么说，其实不足以体现这游戏的魅力

138
00:01:00,166 --> 00:01:01,300
因为正如那句话所说

139
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:03,400
真正的快乐不在于抵达终点

140
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:05,000
而在于旅途本身

141
00:01:05,133 --> 00:01:05,933
说到这里

142
00:01:05,933 --> 00:01:07,933
我们来看看这段旅程为什么特别

143
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:13,266
GTNH 最出名的一点就是等待时间非常长

144
00:01:13,733 --> 00:01:17,066
有些人把这视为设计上的最大缺点

145
00:01:17,066 --> 00:01:18,733
但这恰恰也是它的优势之一

146
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:22,366
因为游戏会逼着你真正搞懂发生了什么

147
00:01:22,366 --> 00:01:24,766
然后再让你自己决定要怎么解决发现的问题

148
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:25,966
举个例子

149
00:01:25,966 --> 00:01:27,966
造出第一批钢往往要花 1 小时

150
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,533
而产量却少得可怜

151
00:01:30,933 --> 00:01:33,466
这会促使玩家去建更多土高炉

152
00:01:33,466 --> 00:01:36,000
并设计整套保障这些高炉持续运转的系统

153
00:01:36,666 --> 00:01:38,600
但如果一味堆量，也会带来新问题

154
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:40,133
比如污染过高

155
00:01:40,166 --> 00:01:43,166
这时你又得投入额外精力去治理

156
00:01:43,166 --> 00:01:47,866
或者你也可以利用这些等待时间，去发展众多可选支线内容

157
00:01:47,866 --> 00:01:50,766
这些内容同样能提供不错的妙妙工具

158
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:52,533
指数式增长

159
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,900
这是我在 GTNH 里最喜欢的一点

160
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,533
规模扩张快得惊人

161
00:01:56,933 --> 00:01:59,600
在花了大量时间手动管理炼钢车间后

162
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:04,600
我们终于做出了速度快 70 倍的自动化电高炉

163
00:02:05,100 --> 00:02:06,466
而它还可以继续升级

164
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:09,800
可以换更好的材料和更精密的电路

165
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:14,000
让它在更高温下运行，把加工速度再提升几百倍

166
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:16,733
但到某个阶段，这些升级仍然不够

167
00:02:16,866 --> 00:02:18,500
所以我们会造更大的版本

168
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:22,066
一次处理数千块锭，而且速度极高

169
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:25,366
最终到了后期，我们会解锁诸神之锻炉

170
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:27,633
这个惊人的多方块机器有自己独立的技能树

171
00:02:27,633 --> 00:02:31,533
你可以通过扩建和运行它获得点数，再用点数购买升级

172
00:02:31,666 --> 00:02:34,066
这就是我们做出万亿钢锭的方式

173
00:02:34,766 --> 00:02:35,600
游戏时长

174
00:02:36,066 --> 00:02:38,266
GTNH 的另一个出名的点是

175
00:02:38,266 --> 00:02:40,066
通关往往需要数千小时

176
00:02:40,133 --> 00:02:41,100
这不算缺点

177
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:44,766
而是你可以长期享受、不会在回过神前就结束的体验

178
00:02:45,466 --> 00:02:46,300
复杂度

179
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:49,600
最后，GTNH 的核心卖点就是复杂度

180
00:02:49,900 --> 00:02:52,800
它并不是那种考验手速或反应的“难”

181
00:02:52,866 --> 00:02:56,166
而是需要极高的问题解决能力与投入度

182
00:02:56,366 --> 00:03:00,066
你遇到的第一个真正挑战，多半是电网管理

183
00:03:00,366 --> 00:03:00,933
在大多数游戏里

184
00:03:00,933 --> 00:03:03,066
你基本是不假思索地把设备接上主电线

185
00:03:03,066 --> 00:03:04,866
（向上合并）

186
00:03:04,866 --> 00:03:06,400
但在 GTNH 里，电力问题会被放大得很明显

187
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:11,066
明显到你最终会迷失在自己搭出的电缆迷宫里

188
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:13,866
你一开始就能在大量电缆里做选择

189
00:03:14,066 --> 00:03:16,000
每种线材成本和参数都不同

190
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:18,566
如果选了不适合负载的电缆

191
00:03:18,566 --> 00:03:20,066
它最后可能会起火

192
00:03:20,366 --> 00:03:22,500
并引发更多连锁问题

193
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,100
每种电缆还有不同电阻

194
00:03:25,266 --> 00:03:26,766
会造成不同的电压损耗

195
00:03:26,766 --> 00:03:28,066
这可能拖慢甚至卡住机器

196
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:31,100
每个配方都有最低功率要求

197
00:03:31,133 --> 00:03:32,366
一旦达不到

198
00:03:32,466 --> 00:03:35,933
机器就会卡住并从头开始

199
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:38,266
但这还只是最好的情况

200
00:03:38,466 --> 00:03:42,000
更大的机器可能卡到必须手动干预

201
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:45,100
正在处理的物品也会被销毁

202
00:03:45,733 --> 00:03:48,500
如果这事发生在循环副产物的产线里

203
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:50,100
问题就会雪上加霜

204
00:03:50,533 --> 00:03:51,766
更糟的是

205
00:03:51,766 --> 00:03:55,700
你不小心给了机器它承受不了的过高电压

206
00:03:55,966 --> 00:03:59,366
而以上这些，还只是 GT 电力管理的基础

207
00:03:59,366 --> 00:04:02,966
据我所知，它的设计深度已经远超多数游戏

208
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:06,466
另一个复杂的布线管理难点是 AE2

209
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:07,400
如果你不熟悉

210
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:12,100
应用能源是几乎所有 MC 整合包都会用的物资管理模组

211
00:04:12,266 --> 00:04:16,266
它不只让你查看箱子、仓库和储罐中的全部物品

212
00:04:16,266 --> 00:04:17,766
还能给其他机器自动补料

213
00:04:17,766 --> 00:04:20,566
甚至支持按需合成和被动合成

214
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:24,666
光这个模组原版内容本身，就够做成一个多集系列

215
00:04:24,666 --> 00:04:29,166
而 GTNH 还在此基础上继续扩展功能，以应对它的任务需求

216
00:04:30,266 --> 00:04:34,100
此外，很多人认为游戏里另一块复杂内容是各种处理产线

217
00:04:34,266 --> 00:04:40,066
你经常得串起几十台机器，才能把一份矿石榨得一滴不剩

218
00:04:40,066 --> 00:04:46,666
另一个常被认为有点复杂的任务，是解开某些机器运作所需的谜题（点名某锻炉上的某物质）

219
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:51,533
在 GTNH 里，你时常需要使用图形化编程

220
00:04:51,566 --> 00:04:52,933
研究红石电路

221
00:04:52,933 --> 00:04:53,966
或者做电子表格

222
00:04:53,966 --> 00:04:56,866
甚至画图，来推导某个系统怎样才能稳定工作

223
00:04:57,066 --> 00:04:57,733
说到这里

224
